The Council met in an emergency session Saturday in New York after US, British and French forces conducted overnight strikes against installations in Syria over chemical weapons use in the country. 
While Russia has condemned the aggression as a blatant disregard for international law and the UN Charter, the United States warned that it was prepared to launch further action if Syria's Government continued to use chemical weapons against its own people. Sherwin Bryce-Pease reports… --SABC--